player.seasonOutlook: Drafted 135th overall this year by the 49ers, Cowing fits the Shanahan "type" to a T. He's a diminutive (5-foot-8 and 168 pounds) speedster who excels as a catch-and-run target in space. Best deployed via the slot, Cowing is unlikely to garner much (if any) volume in 2024, as he's seemingly buried on the depth chart and figures to work behind first-round selection Ricky Pearsall. Given the offense he's a part of, however, he's worth keeping tabs on during the season and could provide late-round value in dynasty formats.
